      • checkOuterKey

        protected boolean checkOuterKey()
        Checks outer key to be alphabetic and of length 10.
        Ignores whitespaces as input.
        Forms outer key to groups of 5 characters seperated by a whitespace.

        If outer key is wrong, set background colour to red.
        If outer key is right, set background colour to white.

        Returns:
        True if and only if outer key has length 10 and outer key is alphabetic, else false.
